  "original_title": "\u0db6\u0daf\u0dd4 \u0dc4\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0d8b\u0daf\u0dc0\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0db1 \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0db0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc4\u0dba\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0db4\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dab",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Investigations on six hundred officials helping tax evaders",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Intelligence agencies have reported facts to the government about more than six hundred customs and income tax officials helping millionaire businessmen and their friends escape the tax net.",
        "Government sources say that these facts have been revealed by a special intelligence report submitted to the government.",
        "Thus, the government has already informed the intelligence department to provide further details regarding these fraudulent officers.",
        "Meanwhile, a special study has revealed to the government that the Sri Lanka Customs and the Inland Revenue Department are losing more than 10 crores of tax that can be collected annually due to their various corruption frauds and irregularities.",
        "In order to prevent this situation, it is reported that the high level of the government has focused on establishing a formal institution for revenue management.",
        "It has been discussed at length in the meeting of the ruling party MPs that was held recently under the chairmanship of President Ranil Wickramasinghe that a large amount of recoverable tax revenues are lost due to the wrongdoings of officials.",
        "The MPs Mahindananda Aluthgamage and Rohitha Abeygunawardena had explained the facts in detail there.",
        "In this meeting, many MPs have pointed out to the President that the country's economic crisis can be solved to a significant extent if the revenue lost due to various frauds is recovered.",
        "It has been learned that the President has stated that the necessary measures will be taken promptly.",
        "In the meantime, more than five thousand people who earn special incomes including doctors, lawyers, assistant class teachers, liquor store owners and gas station owners have reported to the government that they are avoiding paying income tax.",
        "The government has also paid special attention to the proper collection of tax money from these people."
      ],
